definitions: (of an inflatable object) filled up with air, especially by using a pump

examples.text: each wheelbarrow has a pumped up tire ensuring a smooth ride
mouth-inflated balloons are softer than pumped balloons

definitions: (of milk) drawn from the breast using a breast pump, typically in order to feed a baby by means of a bottle

examples.text: the pumped milk was quickly stored in a freezer

shortDefinitions: (of milk) drawn from breast using breast pump

examples.text: the team came out really pumped up
I was so pumped that I overdid everything
